begin_memory_text: Well, we talked about our professions mainly. He told me that he was a retired pilot, and I told him that I taught English as a foreign language. We talked about where we were from and also travel.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation we talked about travel. He told me about a time he and his son took an impromptu trip to Brazil. I shared my experience of living in Costa Rica for a time. It was an interesting conversation.
end_memory_text: We talked about AI, COVID-19, and changes in society and politics. My conversation partner seemed like an intelligent and thoughtful person. He was polite and well-read.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going well. I have a doctor's appointment today where we will go over some test results. I'm not happy about the health condition I have, but I am relieved to be meeting with a doctor about it. Overall, I see my week going very well.
critical_positive: My partner was a kind and courteous person. He seemed quite intelligent, easy-going, and mild-mannered. He put me at ease and had interesting things to talk about. I felt like he listened and was respectful and engaged. We did have things in common like travel and being aware of current events, so that helped.
critical_negative: Oh, I don't know. I don't think it was anything that my conversation partner did. I thought it was a positive experience and that the conversation went well. I always feel a small degree of anxiety meeting anyone new because I worry about not having anything to talk about or not being well-received. That wasn't anything personal regarding my partner though, he was great. Kind and courteous.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we were located and what we were doing - retired, her teaching English remotely.  We then transitioned briefly into a discussion of moving back from Costa Rica because of health issues.  I indicated I had travel to Cost Rica many times.
middle_memory_text: We discussed teaching English remotely and how enjoyable that was for her.  She recommended I get a TLFL Certificate if I wanted to pursue teaching English remotely.  We discussed living in Costa Rica and whether English was commonly spoken outside the tourist areas.  She believed that it was not very common outside the cities and other areas where there were a lot of Americans.
end_memory_text: We discussed how things would be over the next year because of COVID.  Discussed the changes in how people work and some of the potential follow-on effects from remote work such as less commuting to work and how that would lead to other challenges and benefits including less pollution, but also less need for cars (how that would affect car manufacturers).
rest_of_day_open: I expect it to be routine as I decide on how to spend most of my time.  In the mornings I have my personal time and in the afternoons I work on various projects and assist my wife as needed.  I expect to complete a website design project for a friend and continue to work on some tax issues which need to be addressed.  In the evening we enjoy a meal and some TV or a movie via Netflix or Hulu.
critical_positive: It started on time and we where able to quickly "break the ice" and begin discussing experiences in we had a common interest such as Costa Rica and COVID and work.  The conversation was free flowing and open.  We did not pursue issues which could possibly led to strong opinions.  We kept it light.
critical_negative: Did not really have any major issues during the conversation.  Starting off was a slight bit of a challenge as we felt our way with each other.  There were just very brief moments when it looked like we might have run out of things to talk about, but only briefly.
